A&D Growth Remains Robust; Execution Strong

Heico is the largest independent supplier of non- OEM jet engine and aircraft component replacement parts. The size of the Parts Manufacturer Approval (PMA) market is \(\sim 2 - 3\%\) of the aircraft parts replacement market and Heico is \(\sim 2 / 3\) of the PMA market. We see Heico continuing to benefit from the current environment within Aerospace OEM as demand exceeds supply. This potentially extends the life of the current fleet allowing for continued revenue opportunities in the aftermarket. We view Heico as a quality business with a strong management team. We see risk reward balanced as we balance better than expected results, robust growth and execution, and improved sentiment with stock outperformance.
Source: Refinitiv, Morgan Stanley Research

Source: Refinitiv, Morgan Stanley Research, Morgan Stanley Institutional Equities Division. The probabilities of our Bull, Base, and Bear case scenarios playing out were estimated with implied volatility data from the options market as of 27 Aug 2025. All figures are approximate risk- neutral probabilities of the stock reaching beyond the scenario price in either three- months' or one- years' time. View explanation of Options Probabilities methodology here

Our bull case valuation of \(\) 415\(reflects a 2026 EV/EBITDA multiple of\) \sim 42x \(and 2026E EBITDA of\) \ \(1.44bn\) . To arrive at our bull case, we forecast revenue CAGR (FY23A- FY26E) of \(19\%\) and FY26E EBITDA margin of \(29\%\)

We arrive at our PT of \(\) 330\(by using a 2026 EV/EBITDA multiple of\) \sim 36x \(and 2026E EBITDA of\) \ \(1.32bn\) . A \(\sim 36x\) EV/EBITDA multiple is above median levels from 2022- Today of \(\sim 32x\) . We view this time period as a proxy as it takes into account post- Covid time period in which aircraft supply has been limited and demand for aftermarket parts and repairs have been robust. \(\sim 36x\) 2026 EV/EBITDA multiple is largely in line w/ HEI's 2026 EV/EBITDA multiple today.

Our bear case valuation of \(\) 240\(reflects a 2026 EV/EBITDA multiple of\) \sim 29x \(and 2026E EBITDA of\) \ \(1.2bn\) . To arrive at our bear case, we forecast revenue CAGR (FY23A- FY26E) of \(16\%\) and FY26E EBITDA margin of \(\sim 26\%\) .

Equal-weight (E). The stock's total return is expected to be in line with the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12- 18 months.

Not-Rated (NR). Currently the analyst does not have adequate conviction about the stock's total return relative to the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12- 18 months.
